  "name": "Operations/ms-bulk-delete",
  "description": "$bulk-delete conformance tests ported from Microsoft.Health.Fhir.Shared.Tests.E2E.Rest.BulkDeleteTests. $bulk-delete is an async long-running job (DELETE with Prefer: respond-async -> 202 Accepted + Content-Location job-status URL); this engine has no wait-for-completion/polling-loop primitive, so job completion (ResourceDeletedCount Parameters) is NOT verified. What IS reliably testable and asserted here: kick-off acceptance (202 + non-empty Content-Location) at system and type scope, a single best-effort status poll (warningOnly, since the job may finish before or after this one check), and the fully synchronous invalid-search-parameter validation failure (400, no async involved). All fixtures use meta.tag http://ignixa.io/testscript/suite/test|<unique-tag-per-scenario> so each kicked-off job only ever targets its own scenario's resources on a shared server; a defensive teardown re-deletes anything the async jobs may not have finished deleting yet.",
